              "content": "The whole machine — press, moulds, model — is built to be owned and run on Country (Oonchiumpa is the first pathway). We are moving closer to community ownership; we never claim it is done. And the handover is concrete: a community-owned site stands on its own at roughly 75–100 beds a year (site bill ~$24K/yr, ~$329 stays per bed — modelled). Communities already order at that scale.",
