              "content": "The plant moves into community hands.",
              "lineHeight": 1.15,
              "fontFamily": "$font-display",
              "fontSize": 38,
              "fontWeight": "normal"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "fxYLU",
              "name": "small",
              "fill": "$cream-2",
              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "content": "Oonchiumpa is the first pathway. And the queue is real: Palm Island (council, community and PICC), Alice Springs (Oonchiumpa with DEWR, part of their youth program), Utopia (wants the shredder, young people engaged), Tennant Creek (The Community Shed, plastic recycling for social enterprise), among more. A community-owned site stands on its own at roughly 75 to 100 beds a year (modelled). Ownership is a pathway we are walking, not a claim we make.",
              "lineHeight": 1.4,
              "fontFamily": "$font-body",
              "fontSize": 17,
              "fontWeight": "normal"
            }
          ]
        },
